    "17288598": {
      "title": "An Axiomatic Semantics of Concurrent Programming Languages",
      "abstract": "A large body of research on the logic of concurrent programs may be characterized as the \u201caxiomatic\u201d school. Members of this school reason about safety properties (\u201csomething bad never happens\u201d) in terms of invariance, and liveness properties (\u201csomething good eventually does happen\u201d) using temporal logic."
    }
  }
